## §4 · Differential expression analysis and volcano plot

Differential gene expression was assessed using DESeq2 (v1.52.0) on the 
filtered count matrix (14,148 expressed genes after low-count filtering). 
A negative binomial generalized linear model was fit with the design 
`~ batch + condition`, accounting for biological replicate as a covariate. 
Sample-specific normalization factors were derived from per-gene average 
transcript lengths reported by tximport, providing per-gene-per-sample 
correction for library size and effective transcript length. Dispersion 
estimates were calculated using DESeq2's default approach: gene-wise 
maximum-likelihood estimates were shrunk toward a parametric mean–dispersion 
trend, with extreme outliers retained at their original values. Statistical 
significance was assessed using the Wald test with Benjamini–Hochberg 
correction applied across all tested genes.

For the primary contrast (DIV2 + Netrin-1 vs DIV2), differential expression 
results were extracted using `results(dds, contrast = c("condition", 
"DIV2_Netrin", "DIV2"))`. Log2 fold-changes were additionally shrunk using 
the apeglm method (Zhu et al. 2018), which applies an empirical Bayes 
adaptive prior tailored to RNA-seq count distributions. Shrunk log2 
fold-changes were used for the highlighted gene set and downstream 
applications (ranked gene lists, single-gene visualizations) but **not** 
for the volcano plot, where unshrunk fold-changes were preferred to 
faithfully represent effect size distribution. Gene annotation 
(HGNC-style symbols, full names, Entrez IDs) was retrieved from 
`org.Rn.eg.db`; 85.6 % of expressed genes received a SYMBOL annotation.

Two tiers of differentially expressed genes (DEGs) were defined: 
a **relaxed set** of 65 genes (padj < 0.05) was used for functional 
enrichment analyses (sufficient statistical power), and a **strict set** 
of 21 genes (padj < 0.05 and |shrunk log2FC| > 0.585, corresponding to 
1.5-fold change) was used to highlight the most robustly regulated genes 
for individual gene-level visualization.

The volcano plot was constructed in R using ggplot2 (v3.5.x) with ggrepel 
(v0.9.x) for label placement. The x-axis displays unshrunk log2 fold-change 
from DESeq2, symmetrically scaled around zero. The y-axis shows −log10(padj), 
capped at 25 for visual stability of extreme outliers; genes with NA padj 
(DESeq2 independent filtering for low-count genes, n = 549) were excluded. 
Points are colored by regulation direction (red = up, blue = down, 
grey = not significant) and sized by DEG tier (small for non-significant 
genes, medium for relaxed-only, large for strict). Dashed reference lines 
indicate padj = 0.05 and |log2FC| = 0.585 thresholds. Strict-set DEGs 
are labelled with HGNC-style symbols.

