## §X · Statistical methods justification 

### Choice of unshrunk log2 fold change
Log2 fold changes were taken as the raw maximum-likelihood estimates 
from the Wald test (DESeq2 results() output) without empirical Bayes 
shrinkage. All genes passing the combined threshold (padj < 0.05 AND 
|raw log2FC| > 0.585) have baseMean > 19 with low SE, where 
shrinkage has minimal impact. Downstream Gene Set Enrichment Analysis 
was performed using the Wald statistic (which combines effect size 
and significance), providing a robust alternative to shrinkage for 
gene ranking.

### Fold-change threshold rationale  
A 1.5-fold cutoff (|log2FC| > 0.585) was used together with padj < 0.05
to define the highlighted DEG set (n = 25). This more permissive 
threshold than the conventional 2-fold cutoff was selected because 
24-hour Netrin-1 treatment is expected to produce modest 
transcriptional changes consistent with its predominantly 
post-translational signaling mechanism (Tcherkezian et al., 2010).
A relaxed DEG set (padj < 0.05 only, n = 66) was retained for 
visualization and downstream functional analyses.

### Boxplot interpretation
Boxplots display per-sample DESeq2-normalized counts. Per-sample 
variability reflects both biological and technical (batch) components; 
statistical significance is derived from the DESeq2 model with batch 
as a covariate (~ batch + condition).

### GSEA ranking metric
Genes were ranked by the Wald test statistic (stat column from DESeq2 
results), which combines effect size and inverse variance, providing 
optimal power for detecting coordinated subtle changes across gene 
sets (DESeq2 vignette recommendation; Subramanian et al., 2005).

"Gene Set Enrichment Analysis (GSEA) was performed using 
clusterProfiler::gseGO() and gseKEGG() with the following 
parameters: minGSSize = 15, maxGSSize = 500, pvalueCutoff = 0.05, 
pAdjustMethod = 'BH', eps = 0, nPermSimple = 10000, and seed = TRUE 
for reproducibility (set.seed(123)). Genes were ranked by the Wald 
statistic from the DESeq2 results table. For genes with multiple 
Ensembl IDs mapping to the same Entrez ID, the gene with the largest 
|stat| was retained (slice_max). Following enrichment, terms with 
setSize < 15 were excluded post-hoc to enforce statistical robustness 
(Subramanian et al., 2005; Korotkevich et al., 2021)."